Description: CVE-2022-35737 - Fix integer overflow in printf() for multi-gigabyte strings
 Increase the size of loop variables in the printf() implementation to
 avoid integer overflow on multi-gigabyte string arguments to %q, %Q,
 and %w format specifiers. Also add an explicit cast in
 sqlite3StrAccumEnlarge to prevent integer overflow when computing the
 new buffer size.
Origin: upstream, https://sqlite.org/src/info/aab790a16e1bdff7
Bug: https://www.sqlite.org/cves.html#CVE-2022-35737
Author: drh <drh@sqlite.org>
Last-Update: 2022-07-18

